  "bo_system": "Northgate M3",
  "description": "Removal of existing LED advertisement displays and erection of a single, double-sided LED digital advertisement display with a 6m x 4m screen. ",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "Condition : 1 - This permission is for a limited period of 5 years from the date of this consent, after which the double-sided LED digital advertisement display screen and its supporting structure shall cease to be displayed and shall be removed from the land, unless further express consent has subsequently been obtained from the local planning authority to retain it. \r\nReason: In order to enable the local planning authority to review the impact of the advertisement and to ensure it does not have an adverse effect on the amenity of the area, in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the \r\nDevelopment Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021) . \r",
    "Condition : 2 - The double-sided LED digital advertisement shown in approved drawing 05 shall not be erected on the site until such time as the three existing LED digital advertisement displays (namely the portrait orientation display at the \r\neastern end and the `Vï¿½ shaped landscape orientation display at the western end of the Upper Richmond Road frontage of the site) and their supporting structures have been removed from the land and the land made good. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the \r\nrequirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021) . \r\n",
    "Condition : 3 - The interval between successive displays should be instantaneous (0.1 seconds or less), the complete screen should change and there should be no visual effects (including fading, swiping or other animated transition \r\nmethods) between successive displays and sequential advertisements will not change more than once ever ten seconds. The display should include a mechanism to freeze the image in the event of a malfunction. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the \r\nrequirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). \r",
    "Condition : 4 - The maximum steady brightness of the advertisement display shall not exceed 300 candelas per sq. m. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the \r\nrequirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021). ",
    "Condition : 5 - The advertisement signs hereby approved shall not be illuminated between the hours of 2300 and 0600. \r\nReason: To safeguard the amenities of nearby residential properties and the visual amenity of the locality, in accordance with policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) \r\ncoupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).",
    "Condition : 6 - There shall be no special effects (including noise, smell, smoke, animation, moving feature, exposed cold cathode tubing, intermittent lighting, \r\nflashing, scrolling, three dimensional, intermittent or video elements) of any kind during the time that any message is displayed. The use of message sequencing for the same product is prohibited and the advertisements shall not include features/equipment which would allow interactive messages/advertisements to be displayed. \r\nReason: In the interest of highway safety and of the visual amenities of the locality in accordance with Council policy DMS8 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the \r\nrequirements of the National Planning Policy Framework (2021).",
    "Condition : 7 - Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved drawings, details of landscaping, including species, maturity and location of new trees, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. The approved landscape works and planting shall be carried out prior to operation of the advertisement, or in accordance with a programme agreed in writing with the local planning authority. \r\nReason: In the interest of visual amenity and to provide biodiversity benefit, in accordance with Council policies DMS8 and DMO4 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the requirements of the National Planning Policy Framework 2021.",
    "Condition : 8 - Details of the form and location of a minimum of 3 bird boxes and 2 bat boxes shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority. The approved details shall be implemented within 3 months of the operation of the advertisement display. \r\nReason: In the interest of ecological mitigation in accordance with Council policies DMS8 and DMO4 of the Development Management Policies Document (adopted March 2016) coupled with the requirements of the \r\nNational Planning Policy Framework 2021."
  ],
